# KMP PHP Conventions

Follow CakePHP 5.x patterns. Full examples: `.github/copilot-instructions.md`.

## Structure

- Controllers: thin — orchestrate services, authorize, render
- Services: `app/src/Services/` or `plugins/*/src/Services/` for business logic
- Policies: `canAccess`, `canEdit`, `canDelete` in `src/Policy/` and plugin policies
- Migrations: `bin/cake bake migration Name`; never edit committed migrations

## Standards

```php
<?php
declare(strict_types=1);
```

- PSR-12 via PHPCS (CakePHP ruleset); 4 spaces; 120 char lines
- Type hints on parameters and returns; PHPDoc for classes/methods
- Inline docs explain *why*; usage examples belong in `docs/`

## Mailers

Pre-format dates with `TimezoneHelper` before passing to mailers — templates display strings only.

## Authorization

Call `$this->Authorization->authorizeModel()` in controller `initialize()` for model-level checks.

## Testing

- Extend `HttpIntegrationTestCase` for controller tests (CSRF, security token, auth helpers)
- Extend `BaseTestCase` for unit/service tests
- Plugin tests: `PluginIntegrationTestCase` with `PLUGIN_NAME` constant
